TestTimeoutOnSlowAction
/ Verifies timeout.after fires when the wrapped action exceeds the deadline.
/ timer.sleep for 2 seconds with a 100ms timeout → timeout wins, error is ignored,
/ and %timedOut% (set to true at step 0) is asserted true at the end.
- set %timedOut% = true
- timer.sleep ms=2000
    timeout after 100 ms
    on error ignore
- assert %timedOut% equals true
